result.execSummary:
The defendant Zaidah Angelyn Mosley was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).
  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
*Restitution is set at ZERO.
*Fine is set at ZERO.
*Provide DNA sample, if not already done. 
*Pay all mandatory court costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, including the DNA surcharge, during the course of probation to the probation agent. Any remaining balance due at the end of probation will become immediately due or civil judgment to be entered.

*No possession of any firearms or weapons, firearm ammunition, firearm magazine, firearm holster, or any body armor.
*Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.
*The Court informed the defendant of requirements and penalties applicable under s. 941.29(1m) or (4m).
*No possession of any drug paraphernalia for personal use, manufacturing, delivering or for distribution.

*Drivers license suspension is not imposed.
*Department of Corrections must conduct drug and alcohol testing at least 1 time per month for the first year of probation.

*Maintain Absolute Sobriety: No use or possession/use of alcohol or controlled substances without a valid prescription taken in the manner and fashion as prescribed, for defendant or defendants children.
*Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment and successfully complete recommended treatment.

COURT STAYED THE SENTENCES and placed defendant on probation for 2 YEARS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION AS TO COUNT 1:
- Drivers license suspension is not imposed.
- Court ordered defendant to serve 4 MONTHS CONDITION TIME in the House of Correction without goodtime credit; release ONLY for The Day Reporting Center, and inmate work assignments. Court notes a strong objection to electronic monitoring. 

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION AS TO COUNT 1 AND 2:
- Maintain Absolute Sobriety: No use or possession/use of alcohol or controlled substances without a valid prescription taken in the manner and fashion as prescribed, for defendant or defendants children.
- Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment and successfully complete recommended treatment.  
- Department of Corrections must conduct drug and alcohol testing at least 1 time per month for the first year of probation.
- Defendant to notify Department of Corrections agent of all prescriptions within 3 business days/ 72 hours of receiving prescription from medical professional.
- Fill all prescriptions at one pharmacy, unless otherwise approved by Department of Corrections Agent, and notify the Department of Corrections agent of the pharmacy used. 
- No possession of any drug paraphernalia for personal use, manufacturing, delivering or for distribution.
- No possession of any firearms or weapons, firearm ammunition, firearm magazine, firearm holster, or any body armor.
- Restitution is set at ZERO.
- Fine is set at ZERO.
- Provide DNA sample, if not already done. 
- Pay all mandatory court costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, including the DNA surcharge, during the course of probation to the probation agent. Any remaining balance due at the end of probation will become immediately due or civil judgment to be entered.
